SIMPLE: throttle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Throttle
<hw>Throt"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>throat</ets>. See <er>Throat</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
windpipe, or trachea; the weasand.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Steam Engine)</fld> <def>The throttle
valve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Throttle lever</b></col> <fld>(Steam Engine)</fld>,
<cd>the hand lever by which a throttle valve is moved, especially in a
locomotive.</cd> -- <col><b>Throttle valve</b></col> <fld>(Steam
Engine)</fld>, <cd>a valve moved by hand or by a governor for regulating
the supply of steam to the steam chest. In one form it consists of a
disk turning on a transverse axis.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throttle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Throttle
<hw>Throt"tle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Throttled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Throttling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
compress the throat of; to choke; to strangle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Grant him this, and the Parliament hath no more freedom than if it
sat in his noose, which, when he pleases to draw together with one
twitch of his negative, shall <qex>throttle</qex> a whole nation, to the
wish of Caligula, in one neck.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To utter with breaks and interruption, in the manner
of a person half suffocated.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Throttle</qex> their practiced accent in their fears.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To shut off, or reduce flow of, as steam to an
engine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throttle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Throttle
<hw>Throt"tle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To have the throat
obstructed so as to be in danger of suffocation; to choke; to
suffocate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To breathe hard, as when nearly
suffocated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throttler</ent>⟦br⟧
